															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/peppersghost" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1553042); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1553042&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610248677" alt="PeppersGhost" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1553042)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/peppersghost" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1553042); return false;" >PeppersGhost</a></span> <span class="odate time_1549501643 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">07 Feb 2019 01:07</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4144422">
									

<p>The expungements had me concerned at first, but this turned out to be absolutely phenomenal. The page content makes perfect sense in context. The whole thing makes perfect sense in context, even when it's delightfully nonsensical. It's an exceptional execution of an SCP-001 concept that's been staring us in the face for years, yet is only now coming to the surface.</p>
<p>Seriously. This is so, so good. I love everything about this. Brilliant, brilliant.</p>
<p><strong>EDIT:</strong> A number of people on chat were scratching their heads at this one, so here's my take on it (though I feel like it's pretty much confirmed by a couple of the endings).</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;spoiler</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>It's written from the perspective of someone who tried to access the SCP-001 files without having clearance, and was subsequently affected by the Berryman-Langford memetic kill agent that the <a href="/scp-001">hub page</a> threatens you with. Almost the entire article is their perception of what happens after the cognitohazard takes hold; the only exception is the ending where the employee's body is discovered at their desk.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

